":"1372","1490":"1490","1380":"1380","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1356":"1356","1455":"1455","1365":"1365","1376":"1376","1288":"1288","1332":"1332","Wales":"Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]},{"name":"Rhys","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Welsh:  see  Rees  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rees","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Rice  .","German: habitational name from a place in the Rhineland called Rees.","German: from a short form of the personal name   Andreas  ."]}]},{"name":"Marged","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Margaret</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marged verch Rhys was born in 1345, in Wales, her father, Sir Rhys Griffith I, was 57 and her mother, Joan de Somerville, was 40. She had at least 1 son with Philip Dorddu ap Howel."},"et":{"1345–":"1345–Surnud","1325–1380":"1325–1380","1332–Female":"1332–Surnud","1338–1372":"1338–1372","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","1455–1490":"1455–1490","1345–Male":"1345–Surnud","1365–Male":"1365–Surnud","1288–1356":"1288–1356","1305–1376":"1305–1376","1372":"1372","1490":"1490","1380":"1380","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1356":"1356","1455":"1455","1365":"1365","1376":"1376","1288":"1288","1332":"1332","Wales":"Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1345–":"1345–Kuollut","1325–1380":"1325–1380","1332–Female":"1332–Kuollut","1338–1372":"1338–1372","1345–Female":"1345–Kuollut","1455–1490":"1455–1490","1345–Male":"1345–Kuollut","1365–Male":"1365–Kuollut","1288–1356":"1288–1356","1305–1376":"1305–1376","1372":"1372","1490":"1490","1380":"1380","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1356":"1356","1455":"1455","1365":"1365","1376":"1376","1288":"1288","1332":"1332","Wales":"Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1345–":"1345–Décédée","1325–1380":"1325–1380","1332–Female":"1332–Décédée","1338–1372":"1338–1372","1345–Female":"1345–Décédée","1455–1490":"1455–1490","1345–Male":"1345–Décédé","1365–Male":"1365–Décédé","1288–1356":"1288–1356","1305–1376":"1305–1376","1372":"1372","1490":"1490","1380":"1380","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1356":"1356","1455":"1455","1365"